├── sample_data.sql                        # Sample data for testing
└── PROJECT_DOCUMENTATION.md               # Complete project documentation

================================================================================
KEY COMPONENTS
================================================================================

1. MAIN ENTRY POINT
   - Main.java: Initializes database connection and launches IntroInterface

2. USER INTERFACE FRAMES
   - IntroInterface.java: Welcome screen with project information
   - LoginFrame.java: Unified login interface for all user types
   - DashboardFrame.java: Admin dashboard with full system management
   - CompanyAdminFrame.java: Company Admin portal for stock management
   - TechnicianFrame.java: Technician portal for job management
   - CustomerPortal.java: Customer portal for service requests

3. OOP IMPLEMENTATION
   - BaseUser.java: Abstract base class demonstrating inheritance
   - BaseFrame.java: Abstract base class for frame components
   - Model classes: Admin, CompanyAdmin, Technician, Customer
   - Interfaces: Authenticatable, DataManageable

4. DATABASE LAYER
   - DatabaseConnection.java: Singleton pattern for DB connections
   - DatabaseInitializer.java: Creates all tables and initializes schema
   - DAO classes: Data Access Objects for all entities (CRUD operations)

5. UTILITY CLASSES
   - CSVUtil.java: CSV import/export with UTF-8 BOM support
   - UIStyles.java: Consistent UI styling across application
   - UserManager.java: User management and authentication utilities

================================================================================
DATABASE STRUCTURE
================================================================================

Database: H2 Embedded Database
JDBC URL: jdbc:h2:./renewable_energy_hardware;AUTO_SERVER=TRUE

Tables:
1. admin_accounts              - Admin user accounts
2. technician_accounts         - Technician accounts (with approval workflow)
3. company_admin_accounts      - Company admin accounts
4. customer_accounts           - Customer accounts
5. sales_orders                - Sales transactions
6. inventory                   - Inventory items and stock
7. suppliers                   - Supplier information
8. maintenance                 - Maintenance requests
9. stock_requests              - Stock request orders
10. schedules                  - Delivery and maintenance schedules
11. stock_arrivals              - Stock arrival records
12. technician_jobs            - Job assignments for technicians
13. parts_requests              - Parts requests from technicians
14. technician_issues           - Technical issue reports
15. customer_issues            - Customer-reported equipment issues

================================================================================
USER ROLES AND PERMISSIONS
================================================================================

1. ADMIN
   - Full system access and control
   - Manages inventory, sales, suppliers, maintenance requests
   - Approves technician applications and stock requests
   - Assigns technicians to maintenance jobs
   - Generates reports and analytics

2. COMPANY ADMIN
   - Manages company-level operations
   - Creates and tracks stock requests
   - Monitors delivery and maintenance schedules
   - Updates stock arrival records

3. TECHNICIAN
   - Views assigned maintenance jobs
   - Updates job status and completion
   - Requests parts and reports technical issues
   - Requires admin approval for account activation

4. CUSTOMER
   - Submits maintenance service requests
   - Reports equipment issues
   - Tracks request status in real-time
   - Self-registration without admin approval

================================================================================
OOP CONCEPTS IMPLEMENTED
================================================================================

1. ENCAPSULATION
   - Private fields with public getters/setters in all model classes
   - BaseUser, Admin, Technician, Customer, CompanyAdmin

2. INHERITANCE
   - BaseUser → Admin, Technician, Customer, CompanyAdmin
   - BaseFrame → Frame classes (abstract base for common functionality)

3. POLYMORPHISM
   - Method overriding: getRole(), displayInfo() in user subclasses
   - Interface implementation: Authenticatable, DataManageable

4. ABSTRACTION
   - Abstract class: BaseUser, BaseFrame
   - Interfaces: Authenticatable, DataManageable

================================================================================
CORE FUNCTIONALITIES
================================================================================

1. CRUD OPERATIONS
   - Create: Add new records to all tables
   - Read: Query and display all records
   - Update: Modify existing records
   - Delete: Remove records from database

2. CSV IMPORT/EXPORT
   - Export table data to CSV format (UTF-8 BOM for Excel compatibility)
   - Import data from CSV files
   - Proper handling of special characters and quoted values

3. AUTHENTICATION SYSTEM
   - Unified login interface for all user types
   - Role-based access control
   - Password hashing and validation
   - Session management

4. REAL-TIME NOTIFICATIONS
   - Customer → Admin: Maintenance request notifications
   - Admin → Technician: Job assignment notifications
   - Technician → Customer: Job completion notifications
   - Admin → Company Admin: Stock request approval/rejection

5. SEARCH AND FILTER
   - Search functionality across all tables
   - Status-based filtering
   - Real-time search results

================================================================================
HOW TO RUN THE APPLICATION
================================================================================

Prerequisites:
- Java SE 11 or higher
- H2 Database JAR (included in lib/ folder)

Steps:
1. Ensure h2-2.2.224.jar is in the lib/ folder
2. Compile all Java files:
   javac -cp "lib/h2-2.2.224.jar" -d bin app/**/*.java

3. Run the application:
   java -cp "bin;lib/h2-2.2.224.jar" app.Main

Alternative (Windows batch files):
- run_application.bat
- run_admin.bat
- run_customer.bat

Database:
- Database file: renewable_energy_hardware.mv.db
- Auto-created on first run
- Schema initialized automatically via DatabaseInitializer

